1. Question: Which list was easiest to sort and why?
Answer: The sorted list was the easiest to sort because the numbers were already in order. Bubble sort still checked the list
but doesn't have to make any changes

2. Queston: Which list required the most work?
Answer: The reverse order list required the most work since bubble sort had to do every comparison as well as swap every value
into the correct spot

3. Question: Why is sorting useful before searching?
Answer: Sorting is useful before searching because it allows the search code to perform faster

4. Question: When might linear search still be useful?
Answer: Linear search is useful when you only need to search one time, because sorting the list isn't nessecary and takes extra time